ContentDesc_Götterdämmerung - Lakshmi: Upon witnessing her daughter's death at the hands of Fordola and her Skulls, the Qalyana broodmother cried out to the heavens in despair...and a primal answered. Sri Lakshmi, patron deity of the Ananta, came forth from the aether, and the imperials were put to flight. Alas, the tale did not end there, for now the Qalyana demand that the Vira come and pay tribute to the goddess. And so it falls to you and your comrades to journey unto the Qalyana stronghold of Djanan Qhat, and put an end to Sri Lakshmi's dream.
Instancecontenttextdata_16301_Text: A sssliver of grace I bequeath to you...
Instancecontenttextdata_16302_Text: My grace, my beauty, my everything...is yours...
Instancecontenttextdata_16303_Text: I shall free you from your hate!
Instancecontenttextdata_16305_Text: There is no place for you within our dream...
Instancecontenttextdata_16308_Text: Ressst your weary sssouls in my bosom.
Instancecontenttextdata_16309_Text: Partake of my life and my love...
Instancecontenttextdata_16314_Text: Who are you to wake them from the dream...
